description.narrative: Algeria - HIV - Ministry of Health, Population and Hospital Reform of the People's Democratic Republic of Algeria. This program has the following goals: Reduce the number of new infections. Reduce the various forms of HIV-related stigma and discrimination. Stabilize the mortality rate specific to HIV. The objectives of this program are: At least 90% of vulnerable populations (youth, women, mobile populations, PDL, men in uniform) adopt attitudes and practices that protect them from the risk of HIV infection. At least 90% of the populations most exposed to the risk of infection (SWs, MSM, people who inject drugs) adopt attitudes and practices that reduce the risk of HIV transmission
